<plot>After a brief review of the problems described in _Freewayphobia #1 (1965)_ (qv), we see a new range of problems. These include: abrupt breakdowns due to poor maintenance; unsecured loads; running out of gas. We learn how to handle breakdowns properly. We also learn about situations that can affect the driver, like fatigue, alcohol, turnpike trance, and the weather.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?220341</url></doc>
